<p>The Northwest Philadelphia neighborhoods of Mt. Airy and Chestnut Hill contain many larger single-family homes with ample roof space for solar arrays and traditional HVAC systems, making them excellent candidates for comprehensive energy upgrades. South Philadelphia's tight-knit row home communities benefit from mini-split heat pump systems that don't require extensive ductwork modifications, while University City's mix of student housing and family homes creates opportunities for both small and large-scale installations. Each neighborhood's specific building types, roof orientations, and local regulations must be considered when planning solar and HVAC projects to ensure optimal performance and compliance with city requirements.</p>

